# Data-Driven Configuration

- Put tunable gameplay numbers in config assets, not hardcoded constants.
- Use versioned config structures for forward compatibility.
- Validate config at load/startup and fail fast on invalid values.
- Use clear units in names (`seconds`, `meters`, `frames`).

# Config Discipline

- Keep defaults safe and playable.
- Never mix editor-only assumptions into runtime logic.
- Add migration notes when config schema changes.

# Example

```csharp
// BAD
_parryWindow = 0.16f;

// GOOD
_parryWindowSeconds = _combatConfig.parryWindowSeconds;
```
